<section id="one">
  <div class="container wow fadeInUp">
    <div class=" text-xs-center">
        <h2>What We Do</h2>
        <p class="lead">
            Using our platform, you'll be able to ask any number of questions about a set of documents, whether they're words, images, pdfs, or something else, and are provided with a simple interface for people to answer those questions. Instead of going through some other, more laborious process to get that information, with us, you can quickly get everything you need done fast.
            </p>
          </div>
        <div class="card-group">
            <!-- card -->
            <div class="card">
                <div class="card-block">
                    <h4 class="card-title">Simple</h4>
                    <p class="card-text">When dealing with human input, simple is always better. We provide the simplest interfaces for users that allow maximum output with minimum confusion.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
            <!-- card -->
            <div class="card">
                <div class="card-block">
                    <h4 class="card-title">Multipurpose</h4>
                    <p class="card-text">Whether the documents are images, pdfs, text, or anything else, we can handle it.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
            <!-- card -->
            <div class="card">
                <div class="card-block">
                    <h4 class="card-title">Multiuser</h4>
                    <p class="card-text">Getting input from any number of users is super simple, so collecting information from humans over a large number of documents can be easily serialized.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="text-xs-center">
          <hr>
          <%= link_to "Veiw Public Examples", surveys_path, class: "btn btn-primary-outline btn-xl page-scroll wow fadeInUp m-t-3" %>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>
<section id="two" class="bg-alt">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row">
            <div class="col-lg-12">
              <h1 class="m-t-0 text-primary">Use Cases</h1>
              <hr>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
    <div class="container wow fadeInUp">
        <div class="row">
            <div class="col-lg-5 col-md-5">
                <div class="feature">
                    <h4 class="text-uppercase">Getting Training Data</h4>
                    <p class="text-muted m-b-0">
                      Have a bunch of unclassified documents or data that you'd like to run learning algorithms on? Upload the data to the platform, and then use the interfaces to quickly, and with the help of multiple users, classify the documents. When each document has been classified (either once or my any number of the users), download the results!
                    </p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>
